cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CC, cs.CR, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the axiomatization of different logics of algorithmic reduction. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses different types of reduction operations and their associated recurrence operations. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper deals with computability logic and the resource usage of different types of reduction operations. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon the security implications of different types of reduction operations. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also less likely but possible as the paper may discuss the efficiency of different types of reduction operations.
